The paper proposes a machine learning-based method to predict air quality levels using environmental monitoring data and meteorological measurements. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) or Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with time series prediction, which could place it in the Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE) sub-category. The paper also discusses the need for effective ways of creating awareness of real-time air quality levels, which could suggest that it belongs to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) or Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories.
